daemontools-b is a collection of tools for managing UNIX services.  It
is derived from the public-domain release of daemontools by
D. J. Bernstein, which can be found at http://cr.yp.to/daemontools.html

daemontools-b adds numerous enhancements above what daemontools could do
while maintaining backwards compatibility with daemontools.  See the
CHANGES file for more details on what features have been added.

Official release can be found at:

	http://untroubled.org/daemontools-b/

Development versions are available via git from:

	http://untroubled.org/git/daemontools-b.git

============
Installation
============

Adjust the values in the conf-* files if necessary.

Build the programs by running 'make'.

Edit the conf-bin and conf-man files and put the destination directory
for programs and man pages in the first line of each respectively.

As root, run 'make install'.



